        dc:description           "Figs 107–118. Metendosternite, terminal parts and genitalia of Cladiscus liaoi sp. nov. (107–110, 113–115, male; 111, 112, 116–118, female). 107 – metendosternite; 108, 111 – pygidium; 109, 112 – ventrite VI; 110 – spicular fork; 113–115 – male genitalia in lateral (113), ventral (114), and dorsal (115) views; 116–118 – apices of ovipositor in lateral (116), ventral (117), and dorsal (118) views." ;
